BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:oXeADi-5ce0r1RYwWsZKx
SUMMARY:Free Throw
DTSTAMP:20260411T111900Z
DTSTART:20260421T013000Z
DESCRIPTION:Since forming in 2012\, FREE THROW's story has been simple: kee
	p going. New records\, longer tours\, bigger rooms - it's always been anot
	her step upward for the Nashville-based quintet\, whose 2014 debut\, Those
	 Days Are Gone\, has become an era-defining classic in the emo-punk genre\
	, launching them onto global tours with Hot Mulligan and New Found Glory a
	nd slots at Slam Dunk\, Riot Fest\, and The Fest. Every milestone has push
	ed them ahead\, but on their sixth LP\, Moments Before The Wind \\(Wax Bod
	ega\\)\, that constant charge gradually slows\, suspended mid-step\, mid-t
	hought\, mid-life. Recorded with longtime producer Brett Romnes on either 
	end of the sold-out Those Days Are Gone 10-year tour\, the follow-up to 20
	23's Lessons That We Swear To Keep chronicles a surrealist descent into li
	minality: a period of intense personal upheaval colored by loss\, renewal\
	, reflection\, and\, ultimately\, life-altering joy through the impending 
	birth of a child. The 11-song set is disarmingly real\, colored by sonic s
	pontaneity - a swirl of Midwest emo\, sweat-soaked punk fervor\, and crash
	ing alternative rock - but also the sort of achingly vulnerable lyricism f
	ans and critics have come to expect from the band. Through it all\, Moment
	s finds Free Throw still moving\, still growing\, but now\, perhaps more t
	han ever\, acutely aware that the path ahead is neither straight nor obvio
	us. There's a quiet confidence guiding them there into a brand-new era\, r
	eady for whatever the wind blows their way.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.co
	m/events/#/details/free-throw/18151711/2026-04-20T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Ar
	ts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-throw/18151711/2026-
	04-20T00
LOCATION:The Showbox\, 1426 1st Ave.\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:s5W1DNrPAWmeHU4lvAomK
SUMMARY:EMBODIED ALTARS DANCE CLASS
DTSTAMP:20260411T111900Z
DTSTART:20260421T013000Z
DESCRIPTION:EMBODIED ALTARS is an all-levels dance class hosted by Daybreak
	 Star Radio. Designed by Indigenous Chicana artist and El Sueño director\,
	 Alicia Mullikin. Dancers will utilize Indigenous principles within moveme
	nt\, meditation\, and song as a way to practice gratitude\, honor the land
	\, and recognize their ancestors. The class is for those who are intereste
	d in reflection\, intention setting\, and a discovery of their own stories
	. No dance experience necessary. \n\nClass Time: Mondays\, 6:30-8PM \n\nNo
	 class 9/15/25\n\nNo class 10/13/25\n\nVenue: Daybreak Star Indian Cultura
	l Center\n\n5011 Bernie Whitebear Way\,\n\nSeattle\, WA 98199 \n\nSliding 
	Scale: $10-$20\\* per class. Sign Up Now! \n\n  \n\nThis venue is ADA acce
	ssible w/ ADA bathrooms and a wheelchair lift to the second floor. Class w
	ill be held in the ballroom space\, this area has 5 ADA parking spaces.\n\
	nThere are an additional 25 parking spots in our lot\, there is ample park
	ing space along the road leading up to Daybreak star as well as the Discov
	ery Park North Parking lot. \n\nWhat to bring: water\, comfortable clothes
	 to dance in\, journal\, your personal identity\, a desire to explore new 
	pathways and an open mind/heart. \n\nHosted at Daybreak Star Indian Cultur
	al Center\n\nProduced by United Indians of All Tribes Foundation\n\nIn Par
	tnership with El Sueno Dance & Daybreak Star Radio\n\n“Indigenize the Airw
	aves” “Art. Culture. Reclamation.” \n\n\\*Talk to us about BIPOC and Queer
	/LGBTQIA2S\\+ Scholorships\\* \n\nPlease contact @el.sueno.dance on IG for
	 private conversations about this topic.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/e
	vents/#/details/embodied-altars-dance-class/16539055/2026-04-20T00\n\nFrom
	 SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/embodied-altars-dance-cla
	ss/16539055/2026-04-20T00
LOCATION:Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center\, 5011 Bernie Whitebear Way\,
	 Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-arts
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Arts & Culture
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
